  "chapter": {
    "number": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Greetings from Paul and Timothy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother,",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "To Philemon our beloved fellow worker,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "to Apphia our sister, to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church that meets at your",
          {
            "noteId": 4172
          },
          "house:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Philemon’s Faith and Love"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "I always thank my God, remembering you in my prayers,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "because I hear about your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for all the saints."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "I pray that your partnership in the faith may become effective as you fully acknowledge every good thing that is ours in Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "I take great joy and encouragement in your love, because you, brother, have refreshed the hearts of the saints."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Paul’s Appeal for Onesimus"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "So although in Christ I am bold enough to order you to do what is proper,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "I prefer to appeal on the basis of love. For I, Paul, am now aged, and a prisoner of Christ Jesus as well."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "I appeal to you for my child Onesimus,",
          {
            "noteId": 4173
          },
          "whose father I became while I was in chains."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "Formerly he was useless to you, but now he has become useful both to you and to me."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "I am sending back to you him who is my very heart."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "I would have liked to keep him with me, so that on your behalf he could minister to me in my chains for the gospel."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "But I did not want to do anything without your consent, so that your goodness will not be out of compulsion, but by your own free will."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "For perhaps this is why he was separated from you for a while, so that you might have him back for good—"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "no longer as a slave, but better than a slave, as a beloved brother. He is especially beloved to me, but even more so to you, both in person and in the Lord."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "So if you consider me a partner, receive him as you would receive me."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "But if he has wronged you in any way or owes you anything, charge it to my account."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "I, Paul, write this with my own hand. I will repay it—not to mention that you owe me your very self."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "Yes, brother, let me have some benefit",
          {
            "noteId": 4174
          },
          "from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "Confident of your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even more than I ask."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "In the meantime, prepare a guest room for me, because I hope that through your prayers I will be restored to you."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Additional Greetings"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, sends you greetings,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "as do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          "The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.",
          {
            "noteId": 4175
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4172,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "You and Your are singular throughout this letter, except in verses 3, 22, and 25.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 2
        }
      },
